				<div class="paper">
					<h3>Paper Title</h3>
					<p class="authors">Authors</p>
					<p><em>Journal Name</em>, Volume(Issue), Year, Pages.</p>
					<p class="abstract">
						<strong>Abstract:</strong> Brief summary...
					</p>
					<div class="paper-links">
						<a href="#">Publisher</a>
						<a href="#">PDF</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				-->
			</section>

			<section class="research-section">
				<h2>Conference Presentations</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>[Presentation title]. [Conference name], [Location], [Date].</li>
					<li><em>Future presentations will be listed here.</em></li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="research-section">
				<h2>Research Philosophy</h2>
				<p>
					I believe the most impactful accounting research bridges theory and practice. My work 
					aims to address real-world challenges that practitioners face while contributing to 
					theoretical understanding of human behavior in organizational contexts. By combining 
					rigorous experimental methods with insights from psychology and technology, I strive 
					to make accounting systems more effective, human-centered, and responsive to the 
					evolving business landscape.
				</p>
				<p>
					As AI and algorithmic systems become increasingly prevalent in accounting and 
					management, understanding how humans interact with these technologies is crucial. 
					My research provides evidence-based insights to help organizations implement 
					technology in ways that enhance rather than diminish human judgment and well-being.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="research-section">
				<h2>Collaborations & Contact</h2>
				<p>
					I'm always interested in discussing potential research collaborations, especially 
					projects that explore behavioral aspects of accounting, AI in professional services, 
					or innovative experimental designs. If you'd like to discuss research opportunities 
					or have questions about my work, please feel free to reach out.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
